==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Residencia
<hw>Re`si*den"cia</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety>
<def>In Spanish countries, a court or trial held, sometimes as long as
six months, by a newly elected official, as the governor of a province,
to examine into the conduct of a predecessor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Residency</ent>⟦br⟧
